@0 = ~Hello! No time to chat, I have to tend to the sick and wounded.~/*¡Hola! No tienes por qué ser tan sarcástico y grosero.*/
@1 = ~It looks like an infirmary. Can you fix me up?~/*Pareces un aventurero. ¿Podrías entrenarme?*/
@2 = ~Why are there so many sick people here? I hope it's not the plague.~/*¿Por qué hay tanta gente aquí? Háblame de la plaga.*/
@3 = ~Bueno, pues me voy.~
@4 = ~Sorry, <SIRMAAM>.My knowledge is not sufficient for this. Speak to Neurik at the temple, he will surely help you.~/*Lo siento, señor. Ha sido un error. En ese caso, no te molestaré más. Si matas al niño tendré que matarte.*/
@5 = ~The plague? No, of course not. These are common sick people, as well as warriors who have been wounded. If you'll excuse me, I'll mind my own business.~/*La Plaga "No, por supuesto que no." No temas; recibirás tu recompensa una vez me hayas liberado. Creo que te valdría más ocuparte de tus asuntos...*/
@6 = ~Sorry, no time to talk, I have to tend to the sick and wounded.~/*Lo siento, Deekin. Tendrás que encontrar tu propia aventura.*/
@7 = ~You know, I'm an aspiring writer. I've just finished working on a novel based on true events in the life of the great but misunderstood Drizzt Do'Urden. If you have a few minutes, I can read you a passage.~
/*No, me lo quedo. Está en el sótano de una casa en la zona este del Distrito de la Península. Vuelve si encuentras algo y te recompensaré.*/